<section class="bg-parchment ruled"><div class="wrap"><details class="design-logic">
<summary>Design Logic: How These Positions Work Together</summary>
<div class="design-body"><ul>
<li>Data broker regulation establishes the registration and deletion infrastructure that makes all other rules enforceable: you cannot prohibit something you cannot identify.</li>
<li>Ad-tech reform addresses the primary commercial use of broker data, targeting the real-time bidding ecosystem where behavioral profiles are broadcast and monetized.</li>
<li>Behavioral modification rules address the psychological exploitation layer, prohibiting dark patterns, engagement manipulation, and psychographic targeting.</li>
<li>Surveillance pricing rules address the economic extraction layer, prohibiting the use of behavioral profiles to identify and charge each consumer the maximum they will pay.</li>
<li>Algorithmic discrimination rules address downstream harms in consequential decisions, extending FCRA protections to all data broker products used in credit, insurance, employment, and housing.</li>
<li>Enforcement architecture makes all five substantive families credible through proactive audits, escalating sanctions, concurrent state authority, and private rights of action.</li>
</ul></div>
</details></div></section>
